      "lesson title": "Digital Twins and AI: Accuracy vs Risk",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Digital twins are virtual replicas of real-world systems, and when combined with AI, they offer powerful ways to model, predict, and optimise complex processes. However, the accuracy of these simulations depends heavily on the quality of the data feeding into them, and gaps between the virtual model and reality can lead to flawed decisions. This lesson explores the tension between the promise of high-precision AI-driven simulations and the very real risks that emerge when those simulations fall short. You will learn to recognise common sources of inaccuracy, understand how those inaccuracies translate into practical risk, and begin to develop a more critical eye when evaluating digital twin outputs. No prior technical knowledge is required, and the focus throughout is on building confident, grounded judgement rather than deep engineering expertise.",
