          "subtitle": "Core principles to carry forward always.",
          "slidecontent": "• Digital twins are only as reliable as the data and assumptions behind them\n• Gaps between simulated and real-world conditions create genuine risk\n• Always question model accuracy before acting on its outputs\n• Small mismatches compound over time\n• Validate regularly, especially when real-world conditions change\n• Start by identifying one assumption in your current models worth testing"
